## Hail Hazard and Damage

### Formation
Hail forms in the upper regions of actively developing convective storms:
- Strong updrafts (up to 100 mph / 160 kph) lift moisture and debris into the storm  
- Water droplets accumulate and freeze into ice pellets  
- As the ice grows heavier, it eventually falls to the ground as hail  

### Impact
- Property damage typically occurs when hailstones reach **0.75 inches (19 mm)** or larger  
- Severe hail can:
  - Damage vehicles  
  - Destroy roofs  
  - Break windows  
  - Injure people and animals  

